charges.charge_description: 18:1344A.F BANK FRAUD-defendant, purporting to be W.A.M. and to have authority to sign W.A.M.'s name and execute financial tranactions, caused the financial institutions, each of which were insured by the FDIC, to release money in their custody and control to the defendant, her husband, G.B. and others, in the following amounts: $240,299.41, $20,000.00, $10,000.00 and $5,500.00, all in violation of Title 18, USC 1344. (1-4)

18:1028A.F FRAUD WITH IDENTIFICATION DOCUMENTS-defendant did knowingly use without lawful authority, a means of identification of another person, to wit: W.A.M's name, as set forth in Count One of the indictment, in violation of Title 18, USC 1028A. (5)

18:1028A.F FRAUD WITH IDENTIFICATION DOCUMENTS-defendant did knowingly use without lawful authority, a means of identification of another person, to wit: W.A.M's name, as set forth in Count Two of the indictment, in violation of Title 18, USC 1028A. (6)

18:1028A.F FRAUD WITH IDENTIFICATION DOCUMENTS-defendant did knowingly use without lawful authority, a means of identification of another person, to wit: W.A.M's name, as set forth in Count Three of the indictment, in violation of Title 18, USC 1028A. (7)

18:1028A.F FRAUD WITH IDENTIFICATION DOCUMENTS-defendant did knowingly use without lawful authority, a means of identification of another person, to wit: W.A.M's name, as set forth in Count Four of the indictment, in violation of Title 18, USC 1028A. (8)
